# Email Harvester

Email Harvester is a simple script to collect email addresses from websites. You can use it to find possible attack vectors on your site. 

-V1 (Basic Version): uses a simple regular Expression to find Emails inside a String
-V2: requests the content of a website, cleans it up and finds Email addresses using our regex
-V3: user can enter a website, script ist able to follow links on that site and search for addresses on other sites too
-V4: more advanced regex, email addresses are written to file
-V5: user can choose between examining one site or collecting emails from everywhere, hopping from site to site via the found links

Used Libraries
- requests (Python Standard Library)
- re (Python Standard Library)
- bs4 (https://pypi.org/project/beautifulsoup4/)
- sys (Python Standard Library)
